{
  "$version": 1,
  "title": "Default role catalogue",
  "description": "Seeded by `rbac:sync-role-definitions`. UPSERTS one row per (business_type, role_name) into `role_definitions` + the corresponding `roles` row. Every role_definitions row pins its i18n labels, min_tier gate, default_permissions[] set, is_customisable + max_custom_permissions. On TenantProvisioned, `TenantDefaultRoleSeeder` enumerates this catalogue filtered by (tenant.business_type IN business_type_slugs AND tenant.tier >= min_tier) + seeds the matching roles for the tenant.",
  "columns_note": "Fields on each entry: `name` (canonical snake_case role name), `guard_name` ('sanctum' or 'platform_admin'), `is_system` (always true \u2014 catalogue rows are system-shipped), `business_type_slugs[]` (which business_types default-provision this role), `label_i18n` ({en, ar}), `description_i18n` ({en, ar}), `min_tier` (small / medium / business / enterprise), `is_customisable` (can tenants edit the permission set), `max_custom_permissions` (cap on tenant-added perms), `default_permissions[]` (compact permission array).",
